ach subbasin. A validation of the simu- lated soil moisture dynamics for GS1 was carried out using satellite-retrieved soil moisture data, which revealed good agreement. The SWAT model (GS1) also captured the sea- sonal variability of the water balance components at the out- let of the watershed. This study demonstrated the potential to use remotely sensed evapotranspiration data for hydrological model cali- bration and validation in a sparsely gauged large river basin with reasonable accuracy. The novelty of the study is the use of these freely available satellite-derived AET datasets to ef- fectively calibrate and validate an eco-hydrological model for a data-scarce catchment.},
